  "product_overview": "This project evolves an existing Next.js-based learning management system into a commercial-grade LMS platform with a focus on rigorous security enhancements. Key security audit and improvements target middleware access controls, server action authentication/authorization, database client usage, and protection of sensitive user data.",
  "core_goals": [
    "Strengthen access control by enforcing strict role-based middleware restrictions, especially for /admin routes.",
    "Ensure all server actions authenticate users properly and authorize them based on their roles to prevent unauthorized access.",
    "Eliminate IDOR vulnerabilities in all server-side functions to prevent users from manipulating resources they do not own.",
    "Verify no usage or exposure of supabase-admin clients on the client side to avoid privilege escalation attack vectors.",
    "Protect sensitive user data from being leaked to the frontend, including raw passwords, other users' emails, or internal metadata."
  ],
  "key_features": [
    "Middleware security restricting /admin routes strictly to admin role users with tests to simulate unauthorized role access.",
    "Comprehensive auditing and refactoring of all exported server actions for mandatory authentication checks via getUser and role validation.",
    "Implementation of safeguards against Insecure Direct Object References by validating user resource ownership in payloads before processing.",
    "Ensuring Supabase client usage is limited to server-side contexts without any exposure in client bundles.",
    "Scrubbing and filtering user data responses to exclude all sensitive fields before sending to frontend."
  ],
